Task 1: Determine the critical threshold (I→S rate of 90%)

My Results (With the JS Version)

My Results (With the Shiny Version)

Implement Initial Infected

My ChatGPT Request

I have: 
"init_world <- function(model) {
 # the complete function
}" 
Please write a one or two-liner to randomly assign a proportion of the initial agents (given by model$init_R, between 0 and 1) to type 3

ChatGPT Answer

nR <- floor(model$init_R * vcount(agents))
V(agents)$type[sample(vcount(agents), nR)] <- 3

Which I implemented as follows:

V(agents)$type[sample(vcount(agents), floor(model$init_R * vcount(agents)))] <- 3

New Implementations

In run_step()

  # 1A) infectious --> removed
  # 1B) removed --> susceptible
  # 1C) infectious --> susceptible
  # 1D) susceptible --> infectious

In init_world()

  # Initital removed
  
  # Initital infectious 
  c  <- ceiling((m+1)/2)
  ids <- seq_len(m*m)
  x   <- ((ids-1) %% m) + 1
  y   <- ((ids-1) %/% m) + 1
  V(agents)$type[ head(order(sqrt((x-c)^2 + (y-c)^2), atan2(y-c, x-c)), model$init_I) ] <- 2

Now Let’s Explore This ABM!

Getting Serious

Time for a more systematic approach:

simulation  <- list(
  model = "week07_inclass",
  replications = 15,
  tbl_parameter = expand.grid(
    init_R = seq(0, .9, length.out = 10),
    init_I = 5
  ),
  master_seed  = 42,
  max_cores    = 15
)

The result

library(tidyverse)
results <- readRDS("../data/abm-diffusion1/week07_inclass_01.rds")
  
results$df_time_series |> 
  filter(step == 100) |> 
  mutate(
    lower = I_share_mean - qnorm(0.975) * I_share_sd / sqrt(replications),
    upper = I_share_mean + qnorm(0.975) * I_share_sd / sqrt(replications)
  ) |> 
  ggplot( aes(x = init_R, y = I_share_mean)) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = lower, ymax = upper), alpha = 0.2) +
  geom_line(aes(y = 1 - R_share_mean), linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  labs(
    x = "Initial removal share (init_R)",
    y = "Mean infected share at step 100",
    title = "Infection prevalence at step 100 with 95% CI"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_x_continuous(
    breaks = seq(0, 0.9, by = 0.1),
    limits = c(0, 1)   # keep full 0–1 range if you like
  ) +
  theme(
    legend.position = "right"
  )

# Implement Initial Infected

## My ChatGPT Request

```         
I have: 
"init_world <- function(model) {
 # the complete function
}" 
Please write a one or two-liner to randomly assign a proportion of the initial agents (given by model$init_R, between 0 and 1) to type 3
```

## ChatGPT Answer

```         
nR <- floor(model$init_R * vcount(agents))
V(agents)$type[sample(vcount(agents), nR)] <- 3
```

Which I implemented as follows:

```         
V(agents)$type[sample(vcount(agents), floor(model$init_R * vcount(agents)))] <- 3
```

# New Implementations

## In `run_step()`

```         
  # 1A) infectious --> removed
  # 1B) removed --> susceptible
  # 1C) infectious --> susceptible
  # 1D) susceptible --> infectious
```

## In `init_world()`

```         
  # Initital removed
  
  # Initital infectious 
  c  <- ceiling((m+1)/2)
  ids <- seq_len(m*m)
  x   <- ((ids-1) %% m) + 1
  y   <- ((ids-1) %/% m) + 1
  V(agents)$type[ head(order(sqrt((x-c)^2 + (y-c)^2), atan2(y-c, x-c)), model$init_I) ] <- 2
```

# Now Let's Explore This ABM!

## Getting Serious

Time for a more systematic approach:

```
simulation  <- list(
  model = "week07_inclass",
  replications = 15,
  tbl_parameter = expand.grid(
    init_R = seq(0, .9, length.out = 10),
    init_I = 5
  ),
  master_seed  = 42,
  max_cores    = 15
)
```
## The result

```{r}
#| label: fig-X
#| fig-cap: The influence of vaccinated people (initial R) on the spread of the disease. 
library(tidyverse)
results <- readRDS("../data/abm-diffusion1/week07_inclass_01.rds")
  
results$df_time_series |> 
  filter(step == 100) |> 
  mutate(
    lower = I_share_mean - qnorm(0.975) * I_share_sd / sqrt(replications),
    upper = I_share_mean + qnorm(0.975) * I_share_sd / sqrt(replications)
  ) |> 
  ggplot( aes(x = init_R, y = I_share_mean)) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = lower, ymax = upper), alpha = 0.2) +
  geom_line(aes(y = 1 - R_share_mean), linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  labs(
    x = "Initial removal share (init_R)",
    y = "Mean infected share at step 100",
    title = "Infection prevalence at step 100 with 95% CI"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_x_continuous(
    breaks = seq(0, 0.9, by = 0.1),
    limits = c(0, 1)   # keep full 0–1 range if you like
  ) +
  theme(
    legend.position = "right"
  )
```
